          "date": "2025-06-04 19:58:47.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 llite: implement concurrent write lease for mirrors",
        "message": "LU-0000 llite: implement concurrent write lease for mirrors\n\nAdd support for concurrent write leases on mirrored files to\nenable multiple writers to write simultaneously to different\nmirrors while maintaining FLR consistency.\n\nThis introduces:\n- LL_LEASE_CWLCK lease type for concurrent write operations\n- MDS_OPEN_CONCURRENT_WRITE flag for server communication\n- Automatic lease acquisition in ll_file_io_generic() for\n  mirrored files during write operations\n- Integration with existing lease infrastructure\n\nThe concurrent write lease allows multiple file descriptors\nto hold write leases simultaneously on the same mirrored file,\nenabling parallel writes to different mirrors while ensuring\nproper FLR state management on the server side.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0d98124bd8bdebb79c648b57834f9fe34c756ade\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
